# Project Context - Personal Portfolio Website

## 📋 Project Overview
**Hugo-based personal portfolio website** for a software engineer using the **PaperMod theme**. This serves as the central context and navigation hub for all project documentation.

## 🎯 Project Purpose
- Professional portfolio and personal branding website
- Showcase software engineering experience and projects  
- Technical and personal blog platform
- Contact and networking hub

## 📚 Documentation Structure

### 🎨 **Design & User Experience**
- **[Styling Guide](./styling-guide.md)** - CSS architecture, responsive design patterns, visual consistency rules, and component styling standards

### 📄 **Content & Writing**
- **[Content Guidelines](./content-guidelines.md)** - Writing standards, SEO practices, blog categorization, and content creation workflows
- **[Resume Template](./resume-template.md)** - Interactive resume structure, company integration, formatting guidelines, and maintenance procedures

### ⚙️ **Technical Configuration**
- **[Hugo Configuration](./hugo-config.md)** - Hugo setup, PaperMod theme configuration, deployment settings, and troubleshooting guide

## 🗂️ Quick Reference

### **When Working On...**
- **Resume Updates**: → `resume-template.md`
- **Blog Posts**: → `content-guidelines.md` 
- **Styling Changes**: → `styling-guide.md`
- **Site Configuration**: → `hugo-config.md`
- **General Context**: → This file (`project-context.md`)

### **Key Project Files**
- **Configuration**: `config.yaml` (consolidated from TOML)
- **Custom Styles**: `assets/css/extended/resume-wide.css`
- **Main Content**: `content/` directory with markdown files
- **Static Assets**: `static/images/` for photos and icons

## 🎯 Current Implementation Status
- ✅ Interactive resume with collapsible sections
- ✅ Blog categorization (Technical/Random)
- ✅ Professional branding and contact integration
- ✅ Responsive design with mobile optimization
- ✅ Git repository with proper .gitignore
- ✅ Company icons and professional styling

